---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<Layout title="About | My Portfolio" page="about">

      <div class="max-w-7xl  mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 lg:py-20">
    <div class="text-center mb-16 lg:mb-24">
      <h1
        class="text-5xl sm:text-6xl lg:text-7xl xl:text-8xl font-black mb-6"
        style="text-shadow: 3px 3px 0 #29cb17, -2px -2px 0 #0a4b09, 3px -2px 0 #406f40, -2px 3px 0 #75db77;"
      >
        About Me
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl lg:text-2xl text-[#29cb17] max-w-4xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        Get to know me a little better and find out what I am passionate about
      </p>
    </div>

      <!-- PROJECT 1 -->
    <div class="mb-16 lg:mb-24">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-black via-[#1a1010] to-black rounded-2xl overflow-hidden shadow-[0_20px_60px_rgba(0,0,0,0.9)] border border-gray-800 hover:border-lime-500/30 transition-all duration-500">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-0">
          <!-- Image -->
          <div class="order-1 relative overflow-hidden h-[400px] lg:h-auto group">
            <img
              src="/Billeder/pb.JPG"
              alt="Picture of me"
              class="w-full h-full object-cover transition-transform duration-700 group-hover:scale-110"
            />
            <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-black/60 to-transparent lg:opacity-80"></div>
          </div>

          <!-- Content -->
          <div class="order-2 p-8 lg:p-12 xl:p-16 flex flex-col justify-center">
            <h2 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-[#29cb17] mb-6">
              Who am I?
            </h2>

<div class="space-y-4 text-lg text-gray-200 leading-relaxed mb-8">
  <p>
My name is Lærke Buch Nonved, and I’m a Danish student currently studying Visual Communication with a specialization in Coded Design at the Danish School of Media and Journalism. I work in the intersection of design, code, and visual storytelling, with a particular interest in creating digital experiences that feel playful, aesthetic, and human.
  </p>

  <p>
  My work is driven by a curious and experimental approach, where I combine creativity with technical skills through tools and technologies such as JavaScript, P5.js, Three.js, Unity, and Astro. I enjoy developing visual concepts and creating projects that invite interaction, atmosphere, and reflection.</p>

  <p>
 Alongside my studies, I work in a nursery, where I have developed strong skills in collaboration, responsibility, and communication through several years of working closely with children, parents, and colleagues. I also have experience with festival work, coordination, and voluntary project management — including being part of organizing the Mediepuls professional festival at DMJX. </p>
  <p>
    Whether I work with digital media, illustration, code, or physical experiences, I am always interested in creating work that feels thoughtful, engaging, and alive.
  </p>
 
</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

                <!-- Footer -->
<footer class="site-footer mt-10">
  <div class="footer-box">
    <p>© Lærke Buch Nonved portfolio</p>
  </div>
</footer>

    </div>
    
 
</Layout>